Nandi! Nandi!

4
00:00:40,531 --> 00:00:42,328
Get inside.

5
00:00:44,935 --> 00:00:46,664
Go.

6
00:00:54,745 --> 00:00:57,805
- We ain't open for business.
- Shut up, whore.

7
00:00:57,882 --> 00:01:00,316
And you, we don't trade with
at all, Rance Burgess.

8
00:01:00,384 --> 00:01:03,376
You're no longer welcome in this establishment.
You've been told that.

9
00:01:03,454 --> 00:01:07,390
I've been told a great many things.
I'm here for what's mine.

10
00:01:07,458 --> 00:01:09,926
Ain't nothin' here
belongs to you.

11
00:01:09,994 --> 00:01:13,225
You don't get gone, we'll be
well within our rights to drop you.

12
00:01:13,297 --> 00:01:15,731
The only rights you got
are the ones I give you.

13
00:01:17,168 --> 00:01:19,534
- Find the girl!
- She ain't here.

14
00:01:19,603 --> 00:01:24,006
Girl left this moon more than a month ago.
It was you chased her off.

15
00:01:24,074 --> 00:01:27,703
[ Girl Screaming ]

16
00:01:30,815 --> 00:01:32,214
Petaline!

17
00:01:34,218 --> 00:01:37,847
It's a good thing
you haven't left with my baby.

18
00:01:37,922 --> 00:01:41,085
- This baby ain't yours.
- So you keep saying.

19
00:01:42,726 --> 00:01:46,321
- [ Gasps ]
- If this D.N.A. is a match...

20
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:49,366
with mine, know...

21
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:51,867
I will be back
for my baby.

22
00:01:51,936 --> 00:01:55,167
- [ Whimpering ]
- And if I have to...

23
00:01:55,239 --> 00:01:57,366
I'll cut it outta ya.

24
00:01:57,441 --> 00:01:59,705
[ Sobbing ]

25
00:02:04,014 --> 00:02:07,040
Oh, don't worry.

26
00:02:07,117 --> 00:02:10,177
Shh. All right, now.
It'll all work out.

27
00:02:12,923 --> 00:02:15,118
He'll do it too.
He'll do what he says.

28
00:02:15,192 --> 00:02:19,458
- No, he won't. We won't allow it.
- How we gonna stop him, Nandi?

29
00:02:19,530 --> 00:02:22,624
- We'll get help, that's how.
- Help?

30
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:25,225
There's not a soul on this moon
go up against Rance Burgess.

31
00:02:25,302 --> 00:02:27,532
She's right.
Ain't nobody strong enough.

32
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:31,507
And even if there was,
who'd help us?

33
00:02:33,444 --> 00:02:35,309
[ Cocks Gun ]

34
00:02:35,379 --> 00:02:37,404
- [ Inara ] Hi.
- [ Yells ]

35
00:02:37,481 --> 00:02:40,780
- Sorry. Didn't mean to startle.
- You didn't.

36
00:02:40,851 --> 00:02:43,877
I was just, uh-- Bwahh.--
that's more like a--

37
00:02:43,954 --> 00:02:47,913
It's a warrior-like--
Strikes fear into the hearts of--

38
00:02:47,992 --> 00:02:53,430
You know, not altogether wise, sneakin' up
on a fella when he's handling his weapon.

39
00:02:53,497 --> 00:02:57,058
I'm sure I've heard that said.
But perhaps the dining area...

40
00:02:57,134 --> 00:02:59,261
- isn't the place for this sort of thing.
- What do you mean?

41
00:02:59,336 --> 00:03:01,804
- It's the only place with a table big enough.
- Of course.

42
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:05,074
In that case...

43
00:03:05,142 --> 00:03:09,476
every well-bred petty crook knows
that the small concealable weapons...

44
00:03:09,547 --> 00:03:12,311
- always go to the far left of the place setting.
- [ Uncocks Gun ]

45
00:03:15,152 --> 00:03:17,677
Got a distress call coming in.
Some folks asking for help.

46
00:03:17,755 --> 00:03:22,089
Really? Folks asking for help
from us petty crooks.

47
00:03:22,159 --> 00:03:24,923
- Well--
- Maybe I should take that right away.

48
00:03:24,995 --> 00:03:27,828
Well, it's for her.

49
00:03:27,898 --> 00:03:32,028
- Huh?
- The call's for Inara.

50
00:03:32,102 --> 00:03:35,469
- I'll take it in my shuttle.
- All right. I'll send it back there to you.

51
00:03:35,539 --> 00:03:39,168
This "distress" wouldn't happen to be
taking place in someone's pants, would it?

52
00:03:44,782 --> 00:03:48,047
- [ Cocks Gun ]
- Bwahh.

53
00:03:50,421 --> 00:03:53,219
~ Take my love, take my land ~

54
00:03:53,290 --> 00:03:56,748
~ Take me where I cannot stand ~

55
00:03:56,827 --> 00:03:59,819
~ I don't care, I'm still free ~

56
00:03:59,897 --> 00:04:03,731
~ You can't take the sky from me ~

57
00:04:03,801 --> 00:04:06,531
~ Take me out to the black ~

58
00:04:06,604 --> 00:04:09,732
~ Tell them I ain't coming back ~

59
00:04:09,807 --> 00:04:12,742
~ Burn the land and boil the sea ~

60
00:04:12,810 --> 00:04:16,507
~ You can't take the sky from me ~

61
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:28,184
~ There's no place I can be ~

62
00:04:28,258 --> 00:04:31,694
~ Since I've found serenity ~

63
00:04:31,762 --> 00:04:35,254
~ But you can't take the sky from me ~

64
00:04:45,175 --> 00:04:47,370
[ Nandi ]
And I got word you were in the area.

65
00:04:47,444 --> 00:04:49,969
I'm imposing,
but I got no one else to ask.

66
00:04:50,047 --> 00:04:52,777
It sounds like something
this crew can handle.

67
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:56,183
I can't guarantee they'll handle it
particularly well, but--

68
00:04:56,253 --> 00:04:58,380
If they've got guns
and brains at all--

69
00:04:58,455 --> 00:05:00,423
They've got guns.

70
00:05:00,491 --> 00:05:04,427
Payment won't be a problem.
We just ain't equipped for this.

71
00:05:04,495 --> 00:05:07,055
Nandi, it's gonna be all right.

72
00:05:07,131 --> 00:05:09,065
The house will tell you
not to come.

73
00:05:09,133 --> 00:05:11,294
I know they ordered you
to shun me when I left.

74
00:05:11,368 --> 00:05:13,495
The house can-- [ Chinese ]

75
00:05:14,838 --> 00:05:17,898
I would have waved you
long ago. It's just--

76
00:05:17,975 --> 00:05:20,205
It doesn't matter.

77
00:05:20,277 --> 00:05:24,043
[ Chuckles ] Who'd have thought
we'd both end up all the way out here?

78
00:05:24,114 --> 00:05:27,277
- Who'd have thought?
- Let me know what your people say?

79
00:05:27,351 --> 00:05:31,048
- Of course.
- I'll wait to hear from you.

80
00:05:31,121 --> 00:05:34,488
- [ Speaking Chinese ]
- And you.

81
00:05:35,759 --> 00:05:37,784
[ Monitor Beeps ]

82
00:05:39,396 --> 00:05:41,523
I suppose you heard
most of that.

83
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:45,401
Only because
I was eavesdropping.

84
00:05:47,871 --> 00:05:50,465
- Your friend sounds like she's in a peck of trouble.
- She is.

85
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:54,136
And there's no authority on that moon
she can go to. They're totally alone.

86
00:05:54,211 --> 00:05:56,475
Some men might take
advantage of that.

87
00:05:56,547 --> 00:05:58,640
One man.

88
00:05:58,716 --> 00:06:02,777
And she's looking for someone
to come along and explain things to him?

89
00:06:02,853 --> 00:06:04,787
That's essentially it, yes.

90
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:08,654
A whole house
full of Companions.

91
00:06:08,726 --> 00:06:11,092
How are they fixed for payment?

92
00:06:11,161 --> 00:06:16,189
They're not Companions.
They're whores.

93
00:06:17,401 --> 00:06:19,631
Thought you didn't much care
for that word.

94
00:06:19,703 --> 00:06:23,366
It applies. They're not registered
with the guild. They're--

95
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:26,136
- Independent?
- Yes.

96
00:06:27,678 --> 00:06:29,669
If you agree to do this,
you'll be compensated.

97
00:06:29,747 --> 00:06:32,181
I'll see to it.
I've put a little aside.

98
00:06:32,249 --> 00:06:34,979
You can keep your money.
I won't be needing no payment.

99
00:06:38,122 --> 00:06:41,990
Mal, thank you.

100
00:06:43,594 --> 00:06:47,553
I'll contact Nandi at once.
But you will be paid.

101
00:06:47,631 --> 00:06:51,692
I feel it's important that we keep
ours strictly a business arrangement.

102
00:06:55,038 --> 00:06:57,472
- I'll speak with the crew.
- Good.

103
00:07:02,546 --> 00:07:05,071
[ Zoe ]
Those who have a mind are welcome to join.

104
00:07:05,149 --> 00:07:08,710
Those who'd just as soon stay
on the ship can do that too.

105
00:07:08,786 --> 00:07:12,017
Hmm, don't much see the benefit
in gettin' involved...

106
00:07:12,089 --> 00:07:14,956
in strangers' troubles without
a up-front price negotiated.

107
00:07:15,025 --> 00:07:19,086
These people need assistance.
The benefit wouldn't necessarily be for you.

108
00:07:19,163 --> 00:07:22,189
- That's what I'm saying.
- No one's gonna force you to go, Jayne.

109
00:07:22,266 --> 00:07:24,734
As has been stated, this job
is strictly speculative.

110
00:07:24,802 --> 00:07:27,202
Good. Don't know these folks.
Don't much care to.

111
00:07:27,271 --> 00:07:29,068
- They're whores.
- I'm in.

112
00:07:29,139 --> 00:07:32,199
Wash, plot a course.

113
00:07:40,417 --> 00:07:43,614
- [Jayne ] That's the whorehouse?
- Yes.

114
00:07:43,687 --> 00:07:47,123
How come it looks like
a frozen dinner pack?

115
00:07:47,191 --> 00:07:49,591
[ Kaylee ]
Solar sheeting. Cheap power.

116
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:52,527
Hope the whores
are prettier than the house.

117
00:07:54,464 --> 00:07:57,456
- Nandi, darling.
- It's so good to see you, mei-mei.

118
00:07:57,534 --> 00:08:00,867
- You look wonderful.
- And you look exactly the same as the day I left.

119
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:04,374
- How do you do that out here?
- Sheer force of will.

120
00:08:04,441 --> 00:08:07,239
- Nandi, this is Malcolm Reynolds.
- I appreciate your coming.

121
00:08:07,311 --> 00:08:11,873
Well, any friend of Inara's is a strictly
businesslike relationship of mine.

122
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:14,850
This is my first mate, Zoe.
I'll introduce you to the rest later.

123
00:08:14,918 --> 00:08:18,877
- They're good folk.
- Can I start getting sexed already?

124
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:21,424
- Well, that one's kind of horrific.
-[ Inara ] Can we talk business?

125
00:08:21,491 --> 00:08:25,052
In here. The rest of you, there's food
and some liquor at the sideboard.

126
00:08:25,128 --> 00:08:27,926
Make yourselves at home.

127
00:08:32,669 --> 00:08:36,230
Look. They got boy whores.
Isn't that thoughtful?

128
00:08:36,306 --> 00:08:39,104
I wonder if they service
girl folk at all?

129
00:08:39,176 --> 00:08:42,737
- Let's not ask.
- Isn't there a pregnant woman I'm to examine?

130
00:08:42,813 --> 00:08:46,010
[ Wash ] You'd really lie
with someone being paid for it?

131
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:48,574
Well, it's not like
anyone else is linin' up to...

132
00:08:48,652 --> 00:08:52,179
- you know, examine me.
- [Jayne ] Whoo.

133
00:08:52,256 --> 00:08:56,625
My John Thomas is about to pop off and fly
around the room, there's so much tasty in here.

134
00:08:56,693 --> 00:08:59,127
Would be you'd get your most
poetical about your pecker.

135
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:07,270
- You'd be the doctor?
- Yes. This is Petaline.

136
00:09:07,337 --> 00:09:10,363
- Yes, sir.
- She's feeling a might weak right now.

137
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:13,034
All right. Well, let's
get you lyin' down.

138
00:09:13,110 --> 00:09:17,103
- Now that's a plan. Ooh!
- Shepherd?

139
00:09:17,180 --> 00:09:19,546
No, thank you.

140
00:09:19,616 --> 00:09:22,608
We were hoping
we might have a prayer meeting.

141
00:09:22,686 --> 00:09:25,314
We ain't had one in months, except
what Emma here reads out on Sundays.

142
00:09:25,389 --> 00:09:28,187
The last shepherd
to come by was springtime...

143
00:09:28,258 --> 00:09:30,192
and he only read
the one passage.

144
00:09:30,260 --> 00:09:33,229
And he took it out
in trade off both of us.

145
00:09:34,631 --> 00:09:38,192
Everyone's got somebody.

146
00:09:38,268 --> 00:09:40,361
Wash, tell me I'm pretty.

147
00:09:40,437 --> 00:09:43,895
Were I unwed,
I would take you in a manly fashion.

148
00:09:43,974 --> 00:09:46,704
- 'Cause I'm pretty?
- 'Cause you're pretty.

149
00:09:46,777 --> 00:09:49,371
I take it reason
doesn't enter into this?

150
00:09:49,446 --> 00:09:51,846
Not with Rance Burgess.
The man is a taker.

151
00:09:51,915 --> 00:09:54,713
- You think the kid is his?
- I think it's Petaline's.

152
00:09:54,785 --> 00:09:59,154
- But the blood test?
- Well, he did favor Petaline pretty exclusively.

153
00:09:59,222 --> 00:10:02,020
But she had others.
Fifty-fifty, not that it matters.

154
00:10:02,092 --> 00:10:07,189
The man ain't fit to raise a cactus plant.
His barren prairie shrew can't bear him an heir...

155
00:10:07,264 --> 00:10:09,198
so he takes it into his head
to pull it outta us.

156
00:10:09,266 --> 00:10:11,996
- That's not gonna happen.
- I see that's the case.

157
00:10:12,069 --> 00:10:15,732
And you see the way we live here.
Go into town, it's the same.

158
00:10:16,807 --> 00:10:19,037
Some places come up rustic 'cause
they ain't got more than the basics.

159
00:10:19,109 --> 00:10:23,341
Rance Burgess has money enough
to build a city, a real community.

160
00:10:23,413 --> 00:10:26,007
Keeps people living like this
so he can play cowboy.

161
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:30,520
Be the one with the best toys.
Turn this moon into a gorram theme park.

162
00:10:30,587 --> 00:10:34,683
Someone stands up to him--
He means to burn me out.

163
00:10:36,026 --> 00:10:39,223
Yeah, sounds like a fun guy.
I'd like to meet him.

164
00:10:39,296 --> 00:10:43,596
- This won't be solved with talk.
- Well, I'm gonna fight a man,
it helps to size him up.

165
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:47,103
Well, he'll be at the theater tonight.
That's a certainty.

166
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:51,732
And so will I. Inara, think you can
stoop to bein' on my arm?

167
00:10:51,808 --> 00:10:55,107
Will you wash it first?

168
00:10:56,546 --> 00:10:59,811
[ Speaking Chinese ]

169
00:10:59,883 --> 00:11:04,547
So, I told the boy, you take a clean
woman's virtue, you take the woman.

170
00:11:04,621 --> 00:11:07,886
And that's for life.
And the boy said his vows right then.

171
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:10,722
- Took very little persuading on my part.
- [ All Laughing ]

172
00:11:10,794 --> 00:11:14,855
[ Exaggerated Laughing ]

173
00:11:14,931 --> 00:11:17,229
Oh, it's nice to know
there's some places left...

174
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,734
in the 'verse where
old-fashioned values still mean a thing.

175
00:11:19,803 --> 00:11:21,828
- Isn't that right, dear?
- Hmm.

176
00:11:21,905 --> 00:11:25,500
- I don't think I know you.
- Name's Malcolm. Malcolm Reynolds.

177
00:11:25,575 --> 00:11:28,408
And might I just say,
she is quite a beauty.

178
00:11:28,478 --> 00:11:34,178
Well, thank you. Ever had occasion
to handle one of these, Mr. Reynolds?

179
00:11:34,251 --> 00:11:38,085
Silk trigger,
active return bolt laser.

180
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:40,919
Well, it's lighter than it looks.
Thought it would have more heft to it.

181
00:11:40,991 --> 00:11:44,757
Oh, no, don't let that fool you. Won't find
technology like that short of Alliance.

182
00:11:44,828 --> 00:11:47,956
And even their issues
don't yet have the auto-target adjust.

183
00:11:48,031 --> 00:11:49,965
I had that crafted special.

184
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:52,968
Didn't think weapons
such as this were generally legal.

185
00:11:53,036 --> 00:11:56,130
For private owner, I mean.

186
00:11:56,206 --> 00:11:59,869
My husband makes a distinction between
legality and morality, Mr. Reynolds.

187
00:11:59,943 --> 00:12:04,312
- I've said that myself.
- Bending one unjust law is a small thing...

188
00:12:04,381 --> 00:12:06,645
when it comes
to protecting one's family.

189
00:12:06,716 --> 00:12:08,650
I think I understand you.

190
00:12:08,718 --> 00:12:11,516
And as you say,
she is a beauty.

191
00:12:11,588 --> 00:12:17,356
She sure is. Of course,
I was referring to the lady. Ma'am.

192
00:12:21,898 --> 00:12:24,799
[ Beeping ]

193
00:12:24,868 --> 00:12:26,802
Yes.

194
00:12:27,971 --> 00:12:30,201
- Well?
- Well what?

195
00:12:30,273 --> 00:12:32,798
You said you wanted to look him in the eye.
You've done that.

196
00:12:32,876 --> 00:12:36,004
- So, what's the plan?
- The plan is we get back to Serenity...

197
00:12:36,079 --> 00:12:39,242
and we get off this rock
just as fast as we can.

198
00:12:42,519 --> 00:12:46,751
And there can be
no mistake. Good.

199
00:12:46,823 --> 00:12:49,986
- Rance?
- The D.N.A. matches.

200
00:12:51,628 --> 00:12:54,358
The child is mine.

201
00:12:59,202 --> 00:13:02,603
We run.
Math just don't add up.

202
00:13:02,672 --> 00:13:05,368
Our weapons stores aren't exactly
overpowering at the moment...

203
00:13:05,442 --> 00:13:08,036
and I don't much like
what we'd be up against.

204
00:13:08,111 --> 00:13:10,443
Nothing worse than a monster
who thinks he's right with God.

205
00:13:10,514 --> 00:13:14,610
Might turn Burgess away once,
but he'll keep comin'.

206
00:13:14,684 --> 00:13:18,357
He won't stop till he gets
what he thinks is his.

207
00:13:18,490 --> 00:13:20,048
- So we run.
- I understand, Captain Reynolds.

208
00:13:20,125 --> 00:13:24,221
You have your people to think of,same as me.
And this ain't your fight.

209
00:13:24,296 --> 00:13:27,197
I don't believe
you do understand, Nandi.

210
00:13:27,266 --> 00:13:31,225
I said we run. We.
My people, your people...

211
00:13:31,303 --> 00:13:34,295
and whatever bits of precious you got
in this house you can't bear to part with.

212
00:13:34,373 --> 00:13:37,672
We load up Serenity,
and we leave Burgess in the dust.

213
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:49,080
Capt. Reynolds, it took me years to cut this
piece of territory out of other men's hands...

214
00:13:49,154 --> 00:13:51,247
- to build this business up from nothing.
- Nandi.

215
00:13:51,323 --> 00:13:55,589
It's who I am, and it's my home.
I'm not going anywhere.

216
00:13:55,661 --> 00:14:00,462
He'll kill you. Kill every last one of them
if it comes to that.

217
00:14:00,532 --> 00:14:05,128
- And he'll sleep well that night.
- Rance Burgess is just a man...

218
00:14:05,204 --> 00:14:07,695
and I won't let any man
take what's mine.

219
00:14:09,174 --> 00:14:11,802
I doubt you'd do different
in my position.

220
00:14:14,013 --> 00:14:16,345
Well, lady, I must say...

221
00:14:16,415 --> 00:14:19,111
you're my kind of stupid.

222
00:14:19,184 --> 00:14:21,516
Oh, hell, he ain't expectin'
much of a fight.

223
00:14:21,587 --> 00:14:24,351
Might be we catch him
with his drawers low.

224
00:14:24,423 --> 00:14:26,687
He'll probably ride in
by daylight.

225
00:14:26,759 --> 00:14:30,786
But I figure three-point watch,
say, four-hour shift...

226
00:14:30,863 --> 00:14:32,797
just to be on the safe side.

227
00:14:32,865 --> 00:14:36,858
Three point, four hour...
should do it.

228
00:14:36,935 --> 00:14:40,632
- I'm fair handy with a hammer, Captain.
- That so, Shepherd?

229
00:14:40,706 --> 00:14:43,174
Been following the footsteps
of a carpenter for some time now.

230
00:14:43,242 --> 00:14:45,574
I think I can do something
about our fortifications.

231
00:14:46,912 --> 00:14:49,847
Okay, then.
We start shootin'...

232
00:14:49,915 --> 00:14:52,907
he'll most like try to burn us out,
save their sweat and bullets.

233
00:14:52,985 --> 00:14:55,977
- Nandi, what's the water supply like here?
- Underground well.

234
00:14:56,055 --> 00:14:58,353
Pump that draws it up is antiquated,
but it don't break down.

235
00:14:58,424 --> 00:15:01,052
Kaylee, think you can swing
an upgrade for their waterworks?

236
00:15:01,126 --> 00:15:03,651
I'll talk to Serenity,
see what she's got we might use.

237
00:15:03,729 --> 00:15:06,323
- Good. We might wanna scrounge up--
- It's starting.

238
00:15:06,398 --> 00:15:09,367
- And that it is, but time is on the enemy's side--
- Dr. Tan?

239
00:15:09,435 --> 00:15:11,903
Oh, it's starting.
Okay, okay, it's starting.

240
00:15:11,970 --> 00:15:15,030
All right, yeah.
Everybody, relax. Be calm.

241
00:15:15,107 --> 00:15:17,041
Nobody panic.
Everything's gonna be okay. Be all right.

242
00:15:17,109 --> 00:15:19,942
- I got this one, Captain.
- Thanks. Okay. Okay, then.

243
00:15:20,012 --> 00:15:22,879
- [ Claps Hands ]
- Let's get to work, people.

244
00:15:29,521 --> 00:15:32,183
[ Screaming ]

245
00:15:46,171 --> 00:15:49,231
The girls and I
have been talking, Shepherd.

246
00:15:49,308 --> 00:15:53,301
We've been discussing what we'd like said
over us if we should happen to fall.

247
00:15:53,378 --> 00:15:57,747
No. I only bury
the dead, child.

248
00:15:59,118 --> 00:16:01,609
No one here's gonna die.

249
00:16:01,687 --> 00:16:04,281
There's people gonna die.

250
00:16:04,356 --> 00:16:07,450
And with people dyin',
comes guts and screamin'.

251
00:16:07,526 --> 00:16:10,461
That can bring on all sorts of screwed-up behavior
if a person ain't used to it.

252
00:16:10,529 --> 00:16:13,896
When the time comes, most important thing,
keep your wits about you.

253
00:16:13,966 --> 00:16:15,763
Clear?

254
00:16:15,834 --> 00:16:19,429
All right.
Now, these are my favorites.

255
00:16:19,505 --> 00:16:22,065
You're to keep them comin'
till there ain't no more to be had.

256
00:16:22,141 --> 00:16:25,770
I shoot, I run out, you hand me
the next biggest one and so on.

257
00:16:25,844 --> 00:16:29,507
- Is there an understanding here?
- Yes.

258
00:16:29,581 --> 00:16:32,141
All righty, then.
Let's get to work.

259
00:16:37,656 --> 00:16:40,523
All I'm saying is that we're living
pretty deep in the rough and tumble...

260
00:16:40,592 --> 00:16:42,526
and I don't see that
changing anytime soon.

261
00:16:42,594 --> 00:16:45,995
- Nor do I.
- Well, I'm not sure now is the best time...

262
00:16:46,064 --> 00:16:48,498
to bring a tiny little
helpless person into our lives.

263
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:51,297
That excuse is getting
a little worn, honey.

264
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:54,703
It's not an excuse, dear.
It's subjective assessment.

265
00:16:54,773 --> 00:16:57,469
I can't help
that it stays relevant.

266
00:16:57,543 --> 00:17:01,343
I don't give a good go-around
about relevant, Wash, or objective.

267
00:17:01,413 --> 00:17:04,780
And I ain't so afraid of losing something
that I ain't gonna try to have it.

268
00:17:06,118 --> 00:17:09,485
You and I would make
one beautiful baby.

269
00:17:09,555 --> 00:17:14,219
And I wanna meet
that child one day. Period.

270
00:17:17,462 --> 00:17:20,727
- [ Gunshot ]
- [Jayne ] Nothin'. Y'all are pullin'...

271
00:17:20,799 --> 00:17:22,733
not squeezin'
like I said.

272
00:17:22,801 --> 00:17:27,864
Next one don't hit that board
is givin'up a special treat. Dong ma?

273
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:30,238
That man's gonna use up all our credit
before we've earned it.

274
00:17:30,309 --> 00:17:33,767
Well, after you've saved our lives,
you can do some chores maybe.

275
00:17:33,845 --> 00:17:37,246
- I'm a fair hand with a mop.
- So your legend tells.

276
00:17:37,316 --> 00:17:40,911
Truth is, I expected a whole lot more of you
to be taking payment in our trade.

277
00:17:40,986 --> 00:17:42,920
Well, we're not
a conglomeration.

278
00:17:42,988 --> 00:17:46,822
Got a preacher, a married fella,
and the doctor--

279
00:17:46,892 --> 00:17:50,350
Well, he'd have to relax
for 30 seconds to get his play.

280
00:17:50,429 --> 00:17:52,363
That'd be more or less a miracle.

281
00:17:52,431 --> 00:17:54,865
These are fetchin' little pieces.
Any of them work?

282
00:17:54,933 --> 00:17:58,767
Oh, don't got many rounds for the chaplain
there, but the rest will be of use.

283
00:17:58,837 --> 00:18:01,067
This is my favorite.

284
00:18:01,139 --> 00:18:03,334
What's its history?

285
00:18:03,408 --> 00:18:06,707
Violence and crime, sad to say.
What about you?

286
00:18:06,778 --> 00:18:09,076
Similar.

287
00:18:09,147 --> 00:18:12,514
No, I mean when are you planning
to avail yourself of some of our trade?

288
00:18:12,584 --> 00:18:15,075
My girls is clean
and kind-spirited.

289
00:18:15,153 --> 00:18:18,281
Well, I got the--
the job on my mind.

290
00:18:18,357 --> 00:18:21,520
After, I'm sure I'll trade.

291
00:18:21,593 --> 00:18:24,187
They're a fine bunch.

292
00:18:24,263 --> 00:18:28,131
You ain't looked at one of them as long
or lovin' as you looked at those pistols.

293
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:31,101
You're not sly, are you?
'Cause I got my boys.

294
00:18:31,169 --> 00:18:34,002
Sly? No.
I lean toward womenfolk.

295
00:18:34,072 --> 00:18:36,870
Just... one thing at a time.

296
00:18:36,942 --> 00:18:41,038
- Never liked complications.
- Oh, I'm certain of that.

297
00:18:42,714 --> 00:18:44,648
Somethin' to be smilin' at?

298
00:18:44,716 --> 00:18:48,812
I trained as a Companion, remember?
I read people pretty well.

299
00:18:48,887 --> 00:18:51,617
Well, that's nice for you.

300
00:18:51,690 --> 00:18:55,126
She's a hell of a woman,
ain't she? Inara.

301
00:18:55,193 --> 00:18:58,390
Yeah, she's a cherry blossom.
No denyin'.

302
00:18:58,463 --> 00:19:01,955
I expect you know her better than I do.
Comin' up together and all.

303
00:19:02,034 --> 00:19:05,561
Imagine I do. She ever tell you
why she left Sihnon?

304
00:19:05,637 --> 00:19:09,300
- Never asked.
- Yes, you did.

305
00:19:09,374 --> 00:19:11,535
I don't know my own self.

306
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:13,578
I was gone long before.

307
00:19:13,645 --> 00:19:16,409
And I'll tell you,
it was a shock, her leaving.

308
00:19:16,481 --> 00:19:19,109
She was special.

309
00:19:19,184 --> 00:19:22,449
There's 40 women in House Madrassa,
and you'd pick her out in a second.

310
00:19:22,521 --> 00:19:24,682
Could have been house priestess
few years time.

311
00:19:24,756 --> 00:19:27,919
- Is that right?
- Had her eyes on it too.

312
00:19:27,993 --> 00:19:30,826
Very focused.

313
00:19:30,896 --> 00:19:32,830
She's like you
more than a little.

314
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:36,993
And how exactly is that?

315
00:19:37,069 --> 00:19:39,435
She hates complications.

316
00:19:42,774 --> 00:19:45,299
They do crop up though,
don't they?

317
00:19:45,377 --> 00:19:47,971
Such is life.

318
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:50,810
[ Exhales, Screams ]
No!

319
00:19:50,882 --> 00:19:56,047
You're not completely dilated. This should be
pretty quick, but don't try to force it.

320
00:19:56,121 --> 00:19:58,487
- The contractions are still preliminary.
- What's he saying?

321
00:19:58,557 --> 00:20:01,526
- It's gonna be a little while, sweetie.
- Oh, but it hurts!

322
00:20:01,593 --> 00:20:04,528
This child wants to be born.
I know it.

323
00:20:04,596 --> 00:20:06,621
Can you get the green vial
from my bag?

324
00:20:06,698 --> 00:20:09,428
We can dull the pain some.

325
00:20:09,501 --> 00:20:11,901
How many babies
have you actually delivered?

326
00:20:11,970 --> 00:20:14,939
As the primary?
This would be the first.

327
00:20:15,006 --> 00:20:17,372
- You?
- My first too.

328
00:20:17,442 --> 00:20:20,411
- Mine too.
- [ Petaline Groaning ]

329
00:20:20,479 --> 00:20:24,245
- [ Groans ]
- It's gonna be a long night.

330
00:20:24,316 --> 00:20:27,410
- You'll do great, Doctor.
- [ Groaning ]

331
00:20:27,486 --> 00:20:30,080
Who do you think is in there?

332
00:20:31,590 --> 00:20:35,993
It was the dulcimer.

333
00:20:36,061 --> 00:20:38,757
The dulcimer drove you
out of Sihnon?

334
00:20:38,830 --> 00:20:41,321
What, did you kill a dulcimer
in a terrible passion?

335
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,334
Actually, yes.

336
00:20:43,402 --> 00:20:45,336
And now that dulcimer's family
is out to get even.

337
00:20:45,404 --> 00:20:47,770
- I get it.
- [ Chuckles ]

338
00:20:47,839 --> 00:20:52,242
I was at practice. You never stop practicing.
You know, not a true Companion.

339
00:20:52,310 --> 00:20:57,441
Some baroque piece
and the instructor keeps saying...

340
00:20:57,516 --> 00:20:59,450
"You're playing it,
not feeling it."

341
00:20:59,518 --> 00:21:03,887
And the fifth time he said it, I took
the damn thing and smashed it into kindling.

342
00:21:03,955 --> 00:21:06,515
- [ Laughs ]
- And that's when it occurred to me...

343
00:21:06,591 --> 00:21:10,254
that a Companion's life might
just be a little too constricting.

344
00:21:11,630 --> 00:21:14,394
So, I trucked out to the border,
learned to say "ain't,"

345
00:21:14,466 --> 00:21:16,696
came to find work.

346
00:21:16,768 --> 00:21:19,293
Found this place.

347
00:21:19,371 --> 00:21:23,307
- It's a nice place.
- It was a dung heap...

348
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:27,311
run by a pig who had half the girls
strung out on drops.

349
00:21:27,379 --> 00:21:30,644
There's no guild out here.
They let the men run the houses...

350
00:21:30,715 --> 00:21:32,683
and they don't ask
for references.

351
00:21:32,751 --> 00:21:35,117
We didn't get along.

352
00:21:35,187 --> 00:21:37,212
And where's he at now?

353
00:21:39,224 --> 00:21:42,489
Let's just say he ain't playing
the dulcimer anymore, either.

354
00:21:42,561 --> 00:21:45,428
- [ Mal Chuckles ]
- [ Glasses Clink ]

355
00:21:47,899 --> 00:21:50,094
Oh.

356
00:21:50,168 --> 00:21:52,398
You are a remarkable woman...

357
00:21:52,471 --> 00:21:54,735
you don't mind my saying.

358
00:21:57,175 --> 00:22:01,077
Well, as long as it's you saying it
and not my fine rice wine.

359
00:22:01,146 --> 00:22:04,946
Oh, it takes more than a few drinks
to render my judgment blurry.

360
00:22:05,016 --> 00:22:08,645
What about you?
Am I gettin' any prettier?

361
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:11,154
By the minute.

362
00:22:19,831 --> 00:22:22,356
I should check the barricades.
Make sure everyone's ready for--

363
00:22:22,434 --> 00:22:24,698
Everyone's asleep.

364
00:22:24,769 --> 00:22:29,433
Well, them as can...
night before a fight.

365
00:22:31,042 --> 00:22:33,306
- Can you?
- What?

366
00:22:33,378 --> 00:22:35,005
Sleep.

367
00:22:37,182 --> 00:22:42,051
Um, Miss Nandi,
I have a confession to make.

368
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:44,782
Maybe I should get the shepherd.

369
00:22:44,856 --> 00:22:46,790
Well, I ain't sinned yet.

370
00:22:46,858 --> 00:22:50,726
I'd feel a little more than awkward
if he were here when I did.

371
00:22:50,795 --> 00:22:54,492
You expect to accomplish
something sinful then, do you?

372
00:22:55,934 --> 00:22:57,868
If I'm overstepping my bounds,
you let me know.

373
00:22:57,936 --> 00:22:59,870
[ Speaking Chinese ]

374
00:22:59,938 --> 00:23:03,840
Malcolm, I've been waiting for you
to kiss me since I showed you my guns.

375
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:10,978
You okay with this?

376
00:23:11,049 --> 00:23:13,916
I'm just waiting to see
if I pass out.

377
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:17,748
Long story.

378
00:23:17,822 --> 00:23:20,416
- I want you to bed me.
- I guess I mean to.

379
00:23:20,492 --> 00:23:23,825
I ain't her.

380
00:23:26,264 --> 00:23:28,926
Only people in this room
are you and me.

381
00:23:31,102 --> 00:23:33,866
So, my child...

382
00:23:33,939 --> 00:23:37,898
how long has it been
since your last confession?

383
00:23:37,976 --> 00:23:40,968
- Longer than I care to say.
- You gonna remember where everything goes?

384
00:23:41,046 --> 00:23:44,209
Let's just say
I plan to take it real slow.

385
00:24:22,954 --> 00:24:27,050
So, the whore's got herself
a champion, has she?

386
00:24:27,125 --> 00:24:29,059
This great man got a name?

387
00:24:29,127 --> 00:24:31,425
Reynolds. Malcolm Reynolds.

388
00:24:31,496 --> 00:24:36,229
Mm, yes. I've met the man.
How many has he got with him?

389
00:24:36,301 --> 00:24:40,431
Just a few. And only
two real fighters besides hisself.

390
00:24:40,505 --> 00:24:42,666
But they got the girls
stirrin'for a battle.

391
00:24:42,741 --> 00:24:45,801
Oh. I certainly wasn't
expecting a battle.

392
00:24:45,877 --> 00:24:51,076
[ Chuckles ] Seems the Heart of Gold's
got itself a few mercenaries.

393
00:24:51,149 --> 00:24:53,515
- [ Men Laugh ]
- Guess we best call the whole thing off.

394
00:24:53,585 --> 00:24:56,213
[ Chuckles ]

395
00:24:58,390 --> 00:25:01,325
Earned yourself
quite a bag of silver, little kitten.

396
00:25:01,393 --> 00:25:06,763
But I got a few more chores in mind
before you get it.

397
00:25:06,831 --> 00:25:09,425
I'm ready.

398
00:25:09,501 --> 00:25:11,435
Now, Chari here...

399
00:25:11,503 --> 00:25:15,735
she understands
a whore's place, don't she?

400
00:25:15,807 --> 00:25:19,641
But Nandi and those others,
they spit on our town.

401
00:25:19,711 --> 00:25:24,045
They've no respect
for the sanctity of fatherhood...

402
00:25:24,115 --> 00:25:26,549
or decency or family.

403
00:25:26,618 --> 00:25:30,520
They have my child held hostage
to their decadent ways...

404
00:25:30,588 --> 00:25:33,182
and that I will not abide.

405
00:25:33,258 --> 00:25:36,056
We will show them what power is.

406
00:25:36,127 --> 00:25:40,029
We will show them
what their position in this town is!

407
00:25:40,098 --> 00:25:42,157
- [ Men Agreeing ]
- Let us all remember...

408
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:46,533
right here and now
what a woman is to a man.

409
00:25:46,604 --> 00:25:49,232
[ Men Agreeing ]

410
00:25:52,143 --> 00:25:54,373
Get on your knees.

411
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:04,518
[ Men Cheering, Whooping ]

412
00:26:33,818 --> 00:26:35,547
- Um--
- Well--

413
00:26:35,620 --> 00:26:39,215
I-I just had to
tell Nandi about...

414
00:26:39,290 --> 00:26:42,521
um, about time to--

415
00:26:42,594 --> 00:26:45,620
- Big fight today.
- Mal, please.

416
00:26:45,697 --> 00:26:49,463
No, I-- No, I-- Well, I--
Uh, you know, I was up. I got I think insomnia.

417
00:26:49,534 --> 00:26:52,162
So you took to bed
with Nandi. I'm glad.

418
00:26:53,271 --> 00:26:55,432
- Glad?
- Yes.

419
00:26:55,507 --> 00:26:58,408
She's a dear friend and probably
in need of some comfort about now.

420
00:26:58,476 --> 00:27:01,775
- Well, uh--
- One of the virtues...

421
00:27:01,846 --> 00:27:05,577
of not being puritanical about sex
is not feeling embarrassed afterwards.

422
00:27:05,650 --> 00:27:07,618
You should look into it.

423
00:27:07,685 --> 00:27:10,176
Well, I just didn't
want you thinkin'...

424
00:27:10,255 --> 00:27:13,156
that I was taking advantage
of your friend.

425
00:27:13,224 --> 00:27:16,057
She's well worth taking advantage of.
I sincerely hope you did.

426
00:27:17,128 --> 00:27:19,824
So, you're okay.

427
00:27:19,898 --> 00:27:22,992
Well, yeah, why--
why wouldn't you be?

428
00:27:23,067 --> 00:27:25,968
I wouldn't say I'm entirely okay.

429
00:27:26,037 --> 00:27:28,938
I'm a little appalled
at her taste.

430
00:27:46,057 --> 00:27:47,991
[Jayne Sighs ]

431
00:27:48,059 --> 00:27:51,426
[ Sobbing ]

432
00:28:11,094 --> 00:28:14,257
[ Mal On Radio ]
Wash,you there yet?

433
00:28:14,331 --> 00:28:17,027
All but. Nice day
for a last stand, isn't it?

434
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:20,001
Nope. Plan to make
a healthy few stands after this one.

435
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:22,300
Just hoping for some air support
from your quarter, is all.

436
00:28:22,372 --> 00:28:25,739
Couple of low flyovers,
engines tipped earthward at full blast.

437
00:28:25,809 --> 00:28:28,676
Should give our guests somethin' other than
killin' you to think about.

438
00:28:28,745 --> 00:28:32,272
[ Mal On Radio ]
What I like to hear. Out.

439
00:28:32,349 --> 00:28:35,682
Malcolm seem a little funny
to you at breakfast this morning?

440
00:28:35,752 --> 00:28:40,485
Come on, Kaylee.
We all know I'm the funny one.

441
00:28:43,627 --> 00:28:45,561
You ladies and gentlemen
all locked and loaded?

442
00:28:45,629 --> 00:28:47,426
- Locked and loaded. Got it.
- Yes, sir.

443
00:28:47,497 --> 00:28:49,431
Good. Remember shoot the man,
not the horse.

444
00:28:49,499 --> 00:28:52,332
A dead horse is cover.
A live horse, great pile of panic.

445
00:28:52,402 --> 00:28:55,462
[Jayne On Radio ]
Oh, now, girl, that is just plain dirty.

446
00:28:55,539 --> 00:28:57,530
Jayne, you are aware
your radio's transmittin'?

447
00:28:57,608 --> 00:28:59,872
'Cause I don't feel particularly girlish
or dirty at the moment.

448
00:28:59,943 --> 00:29:04,471
Oh. Ah, yeah,
just up here waiting, Captain.

449
00:29:04,548 --> 00:29:06,641
Ready 100%.

450
00:29:06,717 --> 00:29:08,776
[ Mal On Radio ]
Better be.

451
00:29:10,854 --> 00:29:14,085
[ Screams ]

452
00:29:14,157 --> 00:29:17,684
You're stronger than this thing, honey.
I can feel it in your grip.

453
00:29:17,761 --> 00:29:21,527
Petaline, look at me.
This is just a moment in time.

454
00:29:21,598 --> 00:29:24,123
- Step aside and let it happen.
- Mm-hmm.

455
00:29:24,201 --> 00:29:26,260
- [ Groans ]
- How is she, Doctor?

456
00:29:26,336 --> 00:29:28,634
She's at 10 centimeters.
Not long now.

457
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:32,974
[ Groaning ]

458
00:29:36,446 --> 00:29:39,040
Inara, I thought
it was just him that--

459
00:29:41,518 --> 00:29:44,885
Nandi, believe me, I'll be fine.

460
00:29:44,955 --> 00:29:48,118
[ Petaline Groaning ]

461
00:29:51,862 --> 00:29:54,262
[ Petaline Groans ]

462
00:30:06,977 --> 00:30:08,911
[ Cocks Gun ]

463
00:30:15,752 --> 00:30:18,243
Mornin'. How you doin'?

464
00:30:18,321 --> 00:30:20,255
A mite tense.

465
00:30:20,323 --> 00:30:22,814
I'd like you on the balcony with me.
You can see everyone there.

466
00:30:22,893 --> 00:30:24,986
- If anything goes--
- You didn't give me the whole truth.

467
00:30:25,062 --> 00:30:28,429
- About what?
- About her feelings for you.

468
00:30:28,498 --> 00:30:32,366
- I really don't know what--
- [Jayne On Radio ] Mal, looks
like we got imminent violence.

469
00:30:51,488 --> 00:30:53,854
Zoe, Jayne, you seein' this?

470
00:30:53,924 --> 00:30:56,154
[Jayne On Radio ]
Gotta be 30 men out there.

471
00:30:56,226 --> 00:30:59,161
[ Zoe On Radio ] Confirm that,
plus a mounted gun on that hovercraft.

472
00:30:59,229 --> 00:31:01,754
[Jayne On Radio ]
What's that you said about runnin' for it?

473
00:31:01,832 --> 00:31:05,563
Okay, folks, we got no shortage of ugly
ridin' in on us...

474
00:31:05,635 --> 00:31:07,626
but that don't change the plan.

475
00:31:07,704 --> 00:31:10,867
Anybody here goes down, you drag 'em
to the back and get back to shootin'.

476
00:31:10,941 --> 00:31:13,409
Only way to help them
is to finish this.

477
00:31:27,691 --> 00:31:30,353
[ Mal On Radio ] Wash, gonna be
trading injuries in under two minutes.

478
00:31:30,427 --> 00:31:33,521
I'd like my sky
a little less empty.

479
00:31:33,597 --> 00:31:35,758
- Copy that, Mal. We-- We--
- [ Gunshots ]

480
00:31:54,985 --> 00:31:57,453
Open her up, Kozick!

481
00:31:57,521 --> 00:31:59,614
- Cover!
- [ Gunfire ]

482
00:32:18,975 --> 00:32:22,274
Jayne, I do believe that's our first hurdle.
Think you might--

483
00:32:22,345 --> 00:32:24,643
[ Yells ]

484
00:32:24,714 --> 00:32:27,547
- I think I might, Captain.
- Fire!

485
00:32:30,821 --> 00:32:32,618
[ Horse Whinnying ]

486
00:32:46,403 --> 00:32:48,462
[ Speaking Chinese ]

487
00:32:57,714 --> 00:33:00,148
Go!

488
00:33:03,420 --> 00:33:06,583
[ Mal On Radio ]
Wash, where the hell is my spaceship?

489
00:33:11,494 --> 00:33:14,122
[ Horse Whinnies ]

490
00:33:19,603 --> 00:33:25,371
Ruttin' lasers? Book! Zoe!
Second hurdle.

491
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:39,889
- [ Groans ]
- That's it, Petaline. One more push.

492
00:33:39,956 --> 00:33:42,550
- [ Louder Groan ]
- That's the shoulders.

493
00:33:42,626 --> 00:33:44,321
- [ Groans ]
- Good!

494
00:34:01,611 --> 00:34:04,409
-[ Man ] Git. Git.
-[ Man Groaning ]

495
00:34:04,481 --> 00:34:07,416
Jayne, I lost visual on Burgess.

496
00:34:07,484 --> 00:34:10,009
[Jayne On Radio ]
Same here.

497
00:34:25,635 --> 00:34:27,967
Take to right.

498
00:34:36,613 --> 00:34:40,071
- Whoo-hoo!
- Hey. Hey. Get 'im.

499
00:34:41,151 --> 00:34:44,780
Let's go.
Come on, let's get 'im.

500
00:34:47,357 --> 00:34:50,292
- [ Laughs ]
- [ Man ] God!

501
00:34:52,329 --> 00:34:55,093
Try the other side!

502
00:34:56,933 --> 00:34:59,026
- Come on. Open up.
- Got you!

503
00:34:59,102 --> 00:35:02,230
- You-- [ Chinese ]
- Open this door!

504
00:35:02,305 --> 00:35:05,706
Nobody's going...

505
00:35:07,711 --> 00:35:09,736
anywhere.

506
00:35:11,014 --> 00:35:13,778
- It's--
- A boy. Healthy.

507
00:35:16,486 --> 00:35:19,421
Good morning, Petaline.
How's my boy?

508
00:35:20,557 --> 00:35:23,219
[ Crying ]

509
00:35:28,298 --> 00:35:30,664
[ Petaline Screams ]
No.

510
00:35:38,141 --> 00:35:41,838
Rance, most of your men
are either dead, dying or run off.

511
00:35:41,911 --> 00:35:45,677
Oh, well, that don't matter none.
I got what I came here for.

512
00:35:45,749 --> 00:35:47,774
Ain't leavin' here with it.

513
00:35:47,851 --> 00:35:51,787
- This is my blood, woman.
- No, this is your blood.

514
00:35:51,855 --> 00:35:54,949
Now,you hand that child over
nice and slow...

515
00:35:55,025 --> 00:35:57,357
or I'll spill
more than you can spare.

516
00:36:00,663 --> 00:36:02,494
[ Punch Lands ]

517
00:36:48,645 --> 00:36:50,670
Hyah!

518
00:37:02,058 --> 00:37:04,322
[ Gun Beeping ]

519
00:37:22,812 --> 00:37:26,407
- You're gonna pay for what you took.
- She was just a whore.

520
00:37:36,192 --> 00:37:39,753
Petaline, you bring
my baby out right now!

521
00:37:39,829 --> 00:37:43,765
You hear me?
I wanna see my son.

522
00:37:54,611 --> 00:37:57,205
Rance, this is Jonah.

523
00:37:57,280 --> 00:38:02,240
- [Jonah Fussing ]
- Jonah, say hi to your daddy.

524
00:38:05,855 --> 00:38:07,823
Say good-bye
to your daddy,Jonah.

525
00:38:10,627 --> 00:38:14,393
Go on. Go on home!

526
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:20,628
You go with them.

527
00:38:30,146 --> 00:38:35,641
[ Woman ]
~ Amazing grace ~

528
00:38:35,718 --> 00:38:41,918
~ How sweet the sound ~

529
00:38:41,991 --> 00:38:44,755
~ That saved ~

530
00:38:44,827 --> 00:38:47,625
~ A wretch ~

531
00:38:47,697 --> 00:38:51,428
~ Like me ~

532
00:38:52,468 --> 00:38:57,428
~ I once was lost ~

533
00:38:57,507 --> 00:39:03,537
~ But now am found ~

534
00:39:03,613 --> 00:39:07,014
~ Was blind ~

535
00:39:07,083 --> 00:39:13,750
~ But now I see ~

536
00:39:21,464 --> 00:39:23,694
I think those girls
will do all right.

537
00:39:24,767 --> 00:39:26,860
She taught them well.

538
00:39:26,936 --> 00:39:28,927
Yeah.

539
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:32,970
I'm--
[ Clears Throat ]

540
00:39:34,410 --> 00:39:37,811
I'm glad you were with her,
her last night.

541
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:40,212
- I am.
- Yeah, well, I ain't.

542
00:39:42,819 --> 00:39:45,014
Hell, wish I never met her...

543
00:39:45,088 --> 00:39:47,022
then I wouldn't have failed her.

544
00:39:47,090 --> 00:39:49,149
That wasn't the way of it.

545
00:39:50,727 --> 00:39:53,491
That's a kindness.

546
00:39:53,563 --> 00:39:55,861
But nothing you say
will convince me different.

547
00:39:58,034 --> 00:40:00,195
Well, I'm still glad.

548
00:40:03,573 --> 00:40:05,734
So, you weren't before?

549
00:40:11,314 --> 00:40:13,248
Inara.

550
00:40:16,019 --> 00:40:17,953
I ain't lookin'
for anything from you.

551
00:40:18,021 --> 00:40:21,718
I'm just, uh...

552
00:40:21,791 --> 00:40:26,228
just feelin' kinda...
"truthsome" right now.

553
00:40:26,296 --> 00:40:29,561
And, uh...

554
00:40:29,632 --> 00:40:33,124
life's just too damn short
for ifs and maybes.

555
00:40:34,437 --> 00:40:37,531
I learned something from Nandi.

556
00:40:37,607 --> 00:40:40,440
Not just from what happened
but from her.

557
00:40:40,510 --> 00:40:43,411
The family she made...

558
00:40:43,479 --> 00:40:47,472
the strength of her love for them,
that's what kept them together.

559
00:40:51,187 --> 00:40:53,985
When you live...

560
00:40:54,057 --> 00:40:56,321
with that kind of strength...

561
00:40:57,393 --> 00:40:59,327
you get tied to it.

562
00:40:59,395 --> 00:41:02,455
You can't break away.

563
00:41:02,532 --> 00:41:05,399
And you never want to.

564
00:41:06,869 --> 00:41:09,565
There's something--

565
00:41:10,973 --> 00:41:14,875
There's something I should
have done a long while ago.

566
00:41:16,312 --> 00:41:21,011
And I'm sorry, for both of us,
that it took me this long.

567
00:41:26,556 --> 00:41:29,024
I'm leaving.

568
00:42:20,042 --> 00:42:22,977
Grr! Arrgh!



